                            <comment id="12782124" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2009 19:48:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Consider an easy way for the user to back up an elastic HBase cluster to S3. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;distcp is too naive an approach. Compactions rewrite data into new files. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One option is a tool, probably MapReduce in formulation, that incrementally writes new edits (stores and delete markers) into log structured files in S3, and conversely can reply from S3 back into HBase. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another option is to hook replication (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1295&quot; title=&quot;Multi data center replication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1295&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1295&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) at least for the backup piece. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12839138" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 27 Feb 2010 02:23:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Revisit if someone actually wants it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017828" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 13:01:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
